1
00:00:05,522 --> 00:00:07,057
[20th Seoul International Culinary Competition Application Form]

2
00:00:07,057 --> 00:00:10,568
This is my application form from last year.

3
00:00:11,904 --> 00:00:14,639
Why does Yeon Du have this?

4
00:00:18,977 --> 00:00:20,220
It's because of you.

5
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:22,256
I couldn't participate in competition because of you.

6
00:00:22,256 --> 00:00:23,382
What are you talking about?

7
00:00:23,382 --> 00:00:25,250
It sounded like you and Kim Yeon Du were having a huge fight.

8
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:29,343
You were really drunk, but even so, if I were her...

9
00:00:30,956 --> 00:00:33,540
At the fried chicken place...

10
00:00:41,091 --> 00:00:45,786
[Best Mistake 3]

11
00:00:45,786 --> 00:00:48,950
One more order of sausages!

12
00:00:53,395 --> 00:00:58,506
Here's the Outdark with fries and fried tteok.

13
00:00:58,506 --> 00:01:00,601
Enjoy.

14
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:04,090
- Thanks.
- No problem.

15
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:07,017
Ji Hyeon Ho?

16
00:01:07,017 --> 00:01:09,010
Tell me more about what you told me the other day.

17
00:01:09,010 --> 00:01:10,845
What do you mean?

18
00:01:10,845 --> 00:01:11,997
What did I say?

19
00:01:11,997 --> 00:01:13,348
That night.

20
00:01:13,348 --> 00:01:15,450
You thought Kim Yeon Du and I were having a huge fight.

21
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:17,585
Tell me about that.

22
00:01:18,587 --> 00:01:20,656
That night...

23
00:01:20,656 --> 00:01:25,399
You were super drunk, and Kim Yeon Du came to pick you up.

24
00:01:26,954 --> 00:01:29,921
She came to pick me up?

25
00:01:29,921 --> 00:01:31,607
Yes. You don't remember?

26
00:01:31,607 --> 00:01:34,342
Excuse me! We haven't got those sausages yet.

27
00:01:34,342 --> 00:01:35,929
Wait here.

28
00:01:35,929 --> 00:01:38,389
I'll serve them the food and will be right back.

29
00:01:39,082 --> 00:01:40,975
Here are the sausages.

30
00:01:41,752 --> 00:01:44,003
Are the sausages coming?

31
00:01:44,003 --> 00:01:47,355
Here they go again. They're the worst.

32
00:01:52,871 --> 00:01:55,555
Here you go. It's on the house.

33
00:01:55,555 --> 00:01:58,508
So please eat fast and leave.

34
00:01:58,508 --> 00:02:00,786
We have to close up soon.

35
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:13,348
Hey, you shouldn't have missed the competition.

36
00:02:13,348 --> 00:02:16,060
His girlfriend was in an accident.

37
00:02:21,442 --> 00:02:22,909
What is your problem?

38
00:02:22,909 --> 00:02:25,454
Were you trying to kill yourself? Why did you run out all of a sudden?

39
00:02:25,454 --> 00:02:27,321
I'm sorry.

40
00:02:27,321 --> 00:02:29,106
I'm sorry.

41
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:33,084
But you should slow down on a street like this.

42
00:02:33,084 --> 00:02:34,488
What are you saying?

43
00:02:34,488 --> 00:02:36,738
Never mind. How are you going to pay for this?

44
00:02:36,738 --> 00:02:37,737
How!

45
00:02:37,737 --> 00:02:40,469
My wrists hurt, my back hurts... I need to go to the hospital.

46
00:02:40,469 --> 00:02:42,470
How are you going to pay me?

47
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:45,313
Yeon Du! Kim Yeon Du!

48
00:02:46,742 --> 00:02:47,626
Yeon Du.

49
00:02:47,626 --> 00:02:49,919
What happened? A motorcycle accident?

50
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:52,112
Are you all right? Are you hurt?

51
00:02:52,112 --> 00:02:53,990
No. I'm not hurt.

52
00:02:53,990 --> 00:02:56,491
Miss, how are you going to pay for this?

53
00:02:56,491 --> 00:02:57,869
I'm a very busy man!

54
00:02:57,869 --> 00:03:00,930
I will chase you to the end of the earth! Got it?

55
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:03,948
Report this. Call the police!

56
00:03:04,735 --> 00:03:06,977
Sir, you can talk to me.

57
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:09,815
It wasn't a serious accident, right?

58
00:03:09,815 --> 00:03:11,941
She didn't get hurt.

59
00:03:11,941 --> 00:03:15,319
You missed the competition for nothing.

60
00:03:16,105 --> 00:03:19,797
You wasted the entry fee, and the time you spent preparing for it.

61
00:03:19,797 --> 00:03:23,926
You didn't get the credit either and you got scolded by your professor.

62
00:03:23,926 --> 00:03:27,355
He might not be able to transfer to another university.

63
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,000
Hey!

64
00:03:43,273 --> 00:03:44,390
Seriously.

65
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:45,534
He's drunk.

66
00:03:45,534 --> 00:03:47,394
Call his girlfriend to take him.

67
00:03:47,394 --> 00:03:49,145
Okay.

68
00:03:51,048 --> 00:03:52,907
Wake up.

69
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:54,817
[Recent calls: Squirtle]

70
00:03:54,817 --> 00:03:57,352
[Calling Squirtle...]

71
00:03:57,352 --> 00:03:59,655
Hello?

72
00:03:59,655 --> 00:04:01,674
You're Hyeon Ho's girlfriend, right?

73
00:04:01,674 --> 00:04:03,868
I'm a friend of Hyeon Ho.

74
00:04:04,645 --> 00:04:08,720
The thing is, Hyeon Ho is really drunk.

75
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:11,599
Yes, I'll send it to you.

76
00:04:58,473 --> 00:05:00,816
Hey, you're here.

77
00:05:00,816 --> 00:05:04,385
What happened? Why is he alone?

78
00:05:04,385 --> 00:05:07,281
I sent his friends home because you were coming.

79
00:05:07,281 --> 00:05:09,984
I've been watching him.

80
00:05:12,904 --> 00:05:16,450
Did he drink a lot?

81
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:18,818
I wonder if something happened to him.

82
00:05:19,953 --> 00:05:24,654
Well, I think it's because of this.

83
00:05:25,567 --> 00:05:27,043
What's this?

84
00:05:27,043 --> 00:05:30,054
I found this on the table while cleaning the table.

85
00:05:31,489 --> 00:05:34,670
[20th Seoul International Culinary Competition Application Form]

86
00:05:35,469 --> 00:05:39,669
Hey. Were you in an accident or something?

87
00:05:40,407 --> 00:05:42,749
Yes. But how do you know that?

88
00:05:42,749 --> 00:05:44,835
I heard them talking about it.

89
00:05:44,835 --> 00:05:48,815
Ji Hyeon Ho went to help you so he missed the culinary competition.

90
00:05:48,815 --> 00:05:50,541
What?

91
00:05:51,293 --> 00:05:53,369
You didn't know?

92
00:05:53,369 --> 00:05:57,696
You guys are dating but don't talk about things like that?

93
00:05:58,684 --> 00:06:01,177
He didn't tell me.

94
00:06:01,177 --> 00:06:04,472
I think things got messed up because of that.

95
00:06:04,472 --> 00:06:06,991
That's probably why he drank.

96
00:06:18,612 --> 00:06:20,162
Squirtle?

97
00:06:20,162 --> 00:06:23,339
Hey, he's awake.

98
00:06:24,393 --> 00:06:26,936
Take him home safely.

99
00:06:26,936 --> 00:06:30,238
If something like this happens again, talk things through.

100
00:06:30,238 --> 00:06:31,074
Okay?

101
00:06:31,074 --> 00:06:34,950
Don't let him come to my restaurant and stop me from going home on time.

102
00:06:43,345 --> 00:06:45,587
It is you, Squirtle.

103
00:06:52,671 --> 00:06:55,523
Hyeon Ho, were you supposed to go to a culinary competition?

104
00:06:56,508 --> 00:06:58,134
What?

105
00:07:01,555 --> 00:07:04,514
Why didn't you tell me? Why didn't you tell me?

106
00:07:04,514 --> 00:07:05,492
You should've told me!

107
00:07:05,492 --> 00:07:09,869
You should've told me honestly that you couldn't come because of the competition.

108
00:07:09,869 --> 00:07:11,555
Am I wrong?

109
00:07:11,555 --> 00:07:12,632
If you had...

110
00:07:12,632 --> 00:07:15,751
If you had, I wouldn't have asked you to come.

111
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:21,555
And you made me hear it from Heo Jin Su of all people.

112
00:07:21,555 --> 00:07:24,602
You don't trust me?

113
00:07:27,122 --> 00:07:28,806
You...

114
00:07:31,334 --> 00:07:33,519
It's because of you.

115
00:07:35,614 --> 00:07:38,807
I missed it because of you.

116
00:07:40,594 --> 00:07:44,113
Why are you yelling at me?

117
00:07:44,990 --> 00:07:46,515
What?

118
00:08:01,515 --> 00:08:04,316
Do you know how I feel right now?

119
00:08:05,719 --> 00:08:07,778
You have no idea.

120
00:08:08,563 --> 00:08:13,515
Your pride has never been hurt because of your grades or the level of your school.

121
00:08:14,419 --> 00:08:17,329
You've never felt as miserable as I.

122
00:08:19,182 --> 00:08:21,767
I gave up everything for you.

123
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:23,127
- But...
- Hyeon Ho.

124
00:08:23,127 --> 00:08:25,629
Let go of me!

125
00:08:49,371 --> 00:08:52,198
You two were yelling like crazy.

126
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:55,134
I could hear you in the kitchen.

127
00:08:55,936 --> 00:08:59,336
I shouldn't have said anything.

128
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:02,916
It's crazy.

129
00:09:12,227 --> 00:09:14,262
When I count to three, open your eyes.

130
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:16,221
Okay.

131
00:09:17,499 --> 00:09:20,501
One, two, three.

132
00:09:21,369 --> 00:09:24,340
[Ju Ah University's No. 4 Hitter Choi Seung Hyeon will play for a pro baseball team!]

133
00:09:25,657 --> 00:09:27,675
What is this?

134
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,772
I'm going to join a pro baseball team.

135
00:09:37,043 --> 00:09:39,369
I'm sorry.

136
00:09:41,623 --> 00:09:43,840
Is this real?

137
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:46,285
Am I dreaming?

138
00:09:46,285 --> 00:09:48,378
No. Wait.

139
00:09:48,378 --> 00:09:50,731
Is this a hidden camera prank? Where are the cameras?

140
00:09:50,731 --> 00:09:51,724
Where are they?

141
00:09:51,724 --> 00:09:54,018
It's not a prank.

142
00:09:54,018 --> 00:09:56,037
Congratulations, Seung Hyeon.

143
00:09:56,037 --> 00:09:57,847
I knew you'd make it.

144
00:09:57,847 --> 00:10:00,430
Are you going to stay at the camp—

145
00:10:06,006 --> 00:10:07,865
Don't worry.

146
00:10:07,865 --> 00:10:10,300
I will call you every day

147
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:13,061
and come to see you when there's no training.

148
00:10:16,207 --> 00:10:18,350
Are you still insecure?

149
00:10:20,278 --> 00:10:22,047
I mean...

150
00:10:22,047 --> 00:10:26,906
A long-distance relationship is not easy.

151
00:10:26,906 --> 00:10:31,719
Seol and Yeon Du had a really hard time.

152
00:10:41,358 --> 00:10:46,892
I'll try harder to make it easier for you.

153
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:56,555
Okay.

154
00:10:59,793 --> 00:11:01,361
Drink your coffee.

155
00:11:01,361 --> 00:11:02,328
It'll get cold.

156
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:04,971
- You too.
- Okay.

157
00:11:04,971 --> 00:11:07,357
You told her that, but...

158
00:11:09,052 --> 00:11:11,895
You're actually worried, right?

159
00:11:13,556 --> 00:11:15,415
What?

160
00:11:15,415 --> 00:11:18,076
You're being punished for ditching Ah Hun

161
00:11:18,076 --> 00:11:20,929
to hang out with Yu Na alone.

162
00:11:22,565 --> 00:11:25,125
Ah Hun is mad that you ditched me.

163
00:11:25,125 --> 00:11:29,694
But Ah Hun forgives you because Ah Hun is a grown-up.

164
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:32,116
Thanks.

165
00:11:32,116 --> 00:11:34,977
Let Ah Hun give you advice as an adult.

166
00:11:34,977 --> 00:11:38,996
At times like this, you need to reassure her.

167
00:11:38,996 --> 00:11:40,841
Express your feelings more.

168
00:11:40,841 --> 00:11:44,918
Spend more time with her before you go to the camp.

169
00:11:45,647 --> 00:11:49,020
So that Yu Na can stay strong and wait for you.

170
00:11:56,391 --> 00:11:58,575
Why are you looking at me like that?

171
00:11:59,661 --> 00:12:01,328
Nothing.

172
00:12:02,063 --> 00:12:04,848
You do sound like a grown-up.

173
00:12:04,848 --> 00:12:08,700
Ah Hun is a real grown-up, not a fake one.

174
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:11,800
I'm not the young Kang Ah Hun anymore.

175
00:12:20,431 --> 00:12:22,649
Where are you going all of a sudden?

176
00:12:22,649 --> 00:12:25,727
To reassure her.

177
00:12:25,727 --> 00:12:27,771
Bye.

178
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:35,854
He was touched by Ah Hun's words.

179
00:12:38,224 --> 00:12:40,484
Who is it?

180
00:12:47,108 --> 00:12:50,776
What? What brings you here all of a sudden?

181
00:12:52,363 --> 00:12:54,523
I have something to tell you.

182
00:13:04,918 --> 00:13:07,427
What do you want to tell me?

183
00:13:11,925 --> 00:13:14,118
Why do you have this?

184
00:13:14,118 --> 00:13:19,253
I guess I took it by mistake when I was taking care of you when you were sick.

185
00:13:31,970 --> 00:13:34,271
I saw that, and I found out.

186
00:13:36,032 --> 00:13:40,399
What? What did you find out?

187
00:13:44,307 --> 00:13:48,383
I found out what happened that night.

188
00:13:51,589 --> 00:13:54,641
How badly I hurt you.

189
00:14:00,515 --> 00:14:02,249
I'm sorry.

190
00:14:04,394 --> 00:14:06,536
I'm sorry, Yeon Du.

191
00:14:11,484 --> 00:14:14,352
But that night I was really drunk.

192
00:14:14,352 --> 00:14:16,605
I know everything.

193
00:14:16,605 --> 00:14:18,140
What?

194
00:14:19,684 --> 00:14:22,344
I know what cooking means to you.

195
00:14:22,344 --> 00:14:25,773
I know how you got this dream.

196
00:14:25,773 --> 00:14:27,725
Ji Hyeon Ho is taking a written test?

197
00:14:27,725 --> 00:14:31,552
Did you cheat? You always got zero marks, but you suddenly scored full marks.

198
00:14:31,552 --> 00:14:32,797
You didn't think I'd notice?

199
00:14:32,797 --> 00:14:34,123
I have to go to college, Teacher.

200
00:14:34,147 --> 00:14:35,400
Go, please.

201
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:36,693
Please go.

202
00:14:36,693 --> 00:14:37,960
Let's say you get into college.

203
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,954
But what if you cause trouble there?

204
00:14:39,954 --> 00:14:44,372
If I write the recommendation letter for you, it'll put me in an awkward position.

205
00:14:47,103 --> 00:14:50,437
Ji Hyeon Ho. Why haven't you submitted your career goals?

206
00:14:50,437 --> 00:14:53,875
I don't have any career goals.

207
00:14:55,361 --> 00:14:58,538
A young man like you should have a dream, right?

208
00:14:58,538 --> 00:15:00,274
Is there anything you want to do?

209
00:15:00,274 --> 00:15:04,579
Or there must be something you're good at.

210
00:15:04,579 --> 00:15:06,738
There isn't.

211
00:15:07,332 --> 00:15:09,692
I'll give you three days.

212
00:15:09,692 --> 00:15:12,727
Think carefully about it, write it up, and submit it.

213
00:15:12,727 --> 00:15:14,563
Got it?

214
00:15:19,202 --> 00:15:21,854
Is it so wrong that I don't have a dream?

215
00:15:21,854 --> 00:15:25,890
There isn't anything I want to do or I'm good at.

216
00:15:30,355 --> 00:15:32,956
There is.

217
00:15:32,956 --> 00:15:34,050
Squirtle.

218
00:15:34,050 --> 00:15:36,076
Hyeon Ho, you can cook well.

219
00:15:36,076 --> 00:15:38,737
I'm not good at it.

220
00:15:38,737 --> 00:15:42,849
I just cook because you told me to stop with delivery food.

221
00:15:42,849 --> 00:15:46,908
You made me lunch boxes.

222
00:15:46,908 --> 00:15:52,747
To me, your lunch box is so much better than my mom's.

223
00:15:54,795 --> 00:15:58,448
Talking about it makes me crave it again.

224
00:15:59,284 --> 00:16:01,401
Pack me another one tomorrow.

225
00:16:01,401 --> 00:16:04,340
Tomorrow is our lunch box day.

226
00:16:10,420 --> 00:16:12,212
Cooking?

227
00:16:14,582 --> 00:16:16,408
Teacher!

228
00:16:19,279 --> 00:16:21,396
That's why

229
00:16:21,396 --> 00:16:24,833
I wanted to support your dream to become a chef.

230
00:16:25,743 --> 00:16:30,611
I wanted to support you and cherish you as your girlfriend.

231
00:16:32,483 --> 00:16:34,993
But that's not what I was doing

232
00:16:36,212 --> 00:16:39,630
I was dragging you down.

233
00:16:42,719 --> 00:16:49,212
I was ruining everything that's important to you.

234
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:53,553
Is that why you wanted to break up?

235
00:16:55,356 --> 00:16:58,350
Because you thought you were dragging me down?

236
00:17:04,032 --> 00:17:07,400
You should've told me that.

237
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,429
You shouldn't have kept it to yourself and decided on your own.

238
00:17:09,429 --> 00:17:11,097
- What if I had told you?
- Then I would've told you—

239
00:17:11,097 --> 00:17:13,923
You would've said it wasn't true.

240
00:17:15,418 --> 00:17:20,470
You would be too busy looking after me, so you couldn't focus on the things that are important to you.

241
00:17:20,470 --> 00:17:23,566
Then I would feel bad.

242
00:17:23,566 --> 00:17:26,895
You would pretend to be okay again, watching me feeling like that.

243
00:17:32,894 --> 00:17:37,172
We decided to date to be happy.

244
00:17:37,172 --> 00:17:40,716
But we always felt bad.

245
00:17:41,302 --> 00:17:44,796
Our hearts got broken every day.

246
00:17:51,746 --> 00:17:54,489
That's why I wanted to break up.

247
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:58,118
This is the best for us.

248
00:18:03,858 --> 00:18:05,667
Yeon Du...

249
00:18:12,292 --> 00:18:15,677
The things I did for her

250
00:18:18,923 --> 00:18:21,708
made her cry.

251
00:18:27,389 --> 00:18:32,730
[Last semester]

252
00:18:33,538 --> 00:18:35,605
You're going to see your boyfriend?

253
00:18:35,605 --> 00:18:37,558
Yes, we're going to eat fried chicken.

254
00:18:37,558 --> 00:18:40,244
Yeon Du, your boyfriend studies hotel culinary arts?

255
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:41,820
Which college?

256
00:18:41,820 --> 00:18:43,205
Seo Rin College.

257
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:44,481
Seo Rin College?

258
00:18:44,481 --> 00:18:45,833
Where is that?

259
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,017
I've never heard of it.

260
00:18:47,017 --> 00:18:52,985
That's when I thought I didn't want to embarrass her as her boyfriend.

261
00:18:52,985 --> 00:18:57,200
To go to a college that she can proudly tell her friends.

262
00:19:05,510 --> 00:19:06,494
Transfer?

263
00:19:06,494 --> 00:19:09,190
It's impossible with your qualifications.

264
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:12,317
You need better grades.

265
00:19:13,335 --> 00:19:14,428
[Seoul International Culinary Competition]

266
00:19:14,428 --> 00:19:18,530
You need to win something from an international competition.

267
00:19:19,509 --> 00:19:22,094
I need to transfer to another school.

268
00:19:22,094 --> 00:19:26,979
To do that, I needed to win awards.

269
00:19:32,246 --> 00:19:35,206
It wasn't because I missed the contest.

270
00:19:35,206 --> 00:19:37,817
It was because I was worried I might not be able to transfer to another college,

271
00:19:37,817 --> 00:19:44,836
and continue to be an embarrassing boyfriend.

272
00:19:44,836 --> 00:19:47,830
That's what I was upset about...

273
00:20:03,490 --> 00:20:09,420
[Staff Only]

274
00:20:09,420 --> 00:20:12,694
This door cannot be locked by accident.

275
00:20:12,694 --> 00:20:14,913
There's even a lock on the door.

276
00:20:14,913 --> 00:20:18,640
It means someone locked it from the outside.

277
00:20:45,027 --> 00:20:48,846
The festival starts tomorrow. You did a great job, Yeon Du.

278
00:20:48,846 --> 00:20:50,540
Don't mention it.

279
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:52,660
Let's go and finish the room escape set.

280
00:20:52,660 --> 00:20:55,400
I finished the important stuff yesterday.

281
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:57,790
You just need to check things.

282
00:20:57,795 --> 00:20:59,683
Hide these notes.

283
00:20:59,683 --> 00:21:02,485
Oh, okay.

284
00:21:02,485 --> 00:21:04,345
Let's go.

285
00:21:22,715 --> 00:21:25,717
[Hyeon Ho's culinary competition]

286
00:21:25,717 --> 00:21:28,386
Do a good job this time.

287
00:23:22,118 --> 00:23:26,402
Unni Se Hui, you want this on the bookshelf, right?

288
00:23:26,402 --> 00:23:29,215
It's very easy to spot.

289
00:23:29,215 --> 00:23:31,492
Do you think it'll be okay?

290
00:23:33,813 --> 00:23:35,705
Unni Se Hui?

291
00:23:37,024 --> 00:23:39,183
Unni Se Hui?

292
00:23:39,183 --> 00:23:40,685
Unni Se Hui?

293
00:23:40,685 --> 00:23:42,487
Unni Se Hui?

294
00:23:45,380 --> 00:23:49,180
♫ Spread towards you ♫

295
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:54,460
♫ Even if everything disappears like the wind ♫

296
00:23:54,460 --> 00:23:58,190
♫ Even if there are no more ♫

297
00:23:58,990 --> 00:24:00,589
[Next episode]

298
00:24:00,589 --> 00:24:02,157
Kim Yeon Du!

299
00:24:02,157 --> 00:24:03,350
Don't worry.

300
00:24:03,350 --> 00:24:04,694
You thought you wouldn't get caught?

301
00:24:04,694 --> 00:24:05,970
You knew about it all along.

302
00:24:05,970 --> 00:24:08,063
Don't say it too easily.

303
00:24:08,063 --> 00:24:09,089
Come and sit.

304
00:24:09,089 --> 00:24:10,810
The seat next to your boyfriend is empty.

305
00:24:10,810 --> 00:24:12,780
♫ You're like the midday sun ♫

306
00:24:12,780 --> 00:24:17,110
♫ Shine brightly on me ♫

307
00:24:17,110 --> 00:24:20,720
♫ I come to you like a fire ♫

308
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:24,240
♫ Like a fire ♫

309
